SIMPLE: methodical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Methodical
<hw>Me*thod"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>methodicus</ets>, Gr.
<?/: cf. F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧thodique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Arranged with regard to method; disposed in a suitable manner, or
in a manner to illustrate a subject, or to facilitate practical
observation; well-ordered; <as>as, the <ex>methodical</ex> arrangement
of arguments; a <ex>methodical</ex> treatise.</as></def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Methodical</xex> regularity.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Proceeding with regard to method; characterized by
method or orderliness; systematic; <as>as, a <ex>methodical</ex>
investigation</as>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns> ⟦ldquo⟧Aristotle, strict,
<xex>methodic</xex>, and orderly.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Harris.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the ancient school of physicians
called methodists.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Me*thod"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Me*thod"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Methodios</ent>⟦br⟧
